y used to reduce label density. In this example, we use it to demonstrate how a numeric attribute can be used for styling with the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" expression. POIs with a rank between 0 and 10 get a red color, between 10 and 20 green, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class DDSCircleLayerExample: UIViewController, MLNMapViewDelegate {","    var mapView: MLNMapView!","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        super.viewDidLoad()","","        mapView = MLNMapView(frame: view.bounds, styleURL: AMERICANA_STYLE)","        mapView.autoresizingMask = [.flexibleWidth, .flexibleHeight]","        mapView.tintColor = .darkGray","","        \/\/ Set the mapâ€™s center coordinate and zoom level.","        let innsbruck = CLLocationCoordinate2D(latitude: 47.26497, longitude: 11.4088)","        mapView.setCenter(innsbruck, animated: false)","        mapView.zoomLevel = 14","","        mapView.delegate = self","        view.addSubview(mapView)","    }","","    \/\/ Wait until the style is loaded before modifying the map style.","    func mapView(_: MLNMapView, didFinishLoading style: MLNStyle) {","        let source = MLNVectorTileSource(identifier: \"demotiles\", configurationURL: URL(string: \"https:\/\/demotiles.maplibre.org\/tiles-omt\/tiles.json\")!)","","        style.addSource(source)","","        let layer = MLNCircleStyleLayer(identifier: \"poi-shop-style\", source: source)","","        layer.sourceLayerIdentifier = \"poi\"","        layer.predicate = NSPredicate(format: \"class == %@\", \"shop\")","","        \/\/ Style the circle layer color based on the rank","        layer.circleColor = NSExpression(mglJSONObject: [\"step\", [\"get\", \"rank\"], 0, \"red\", 10, \"green\", 20, \"blue\", 30, \"purple\", 40, \"yellow\"] as [Any])","        layer.circleRadius = NSExpression(forConstantValue: 3)","","        style.addLayer(layer)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"DDSCircleLayerExample.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Map data from OpenStreetMap. Style uses OpenMapTiles."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"Vector Tile Sources","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Add and style a vector tile source"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/ddscirclelayerexample"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/POIAlongRouteExample":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/POIAlongRouteExample","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/poialongrouteexample","abstract":[{"text":"Use an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSPredicate"},{"text":" to show POI and road labels along a route.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","type":"topic","title":"POI Along a Route","kind":"article"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS/GeoJSON":{"title":"Working with GeoJSON Data","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/geojson","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","role":"article","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[]},"https://maplibre.org/maplibre-style-spec/expressions/#step":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"step"}],"url":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step","title":"step","identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/expressions\/#step"},"https://openmaptiles.org/schema/#poi":{"identifier":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/openmaptiles.org\/schema\/#poi","title":"POIs","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"te